Our work differs from the above discussed previous works by proposing a ) a distributed proxy-based architecture to decrease bandwidth requirements at the clients and the servers without requiring the proxies to keep state information about the whole game space , b ) a dynamic authority assignment technique to reduce latency ( by performing consistency checks locally at the client whenever possible ) by splitting the authority between the clients and servers on a per object basis , and c ) proposing that cheat detection can be built into the proxies if they are provided more information about the specific 